data.name: smoothLabel10.HelpText
data.value: Try this setting when Asterisk is on a public IP, communicating with devices hidden behind a NAT device (broadband router). If you have one-way audio problems, you usually have problems with your NAT configuration or your firewall's support of SIP+RTP ports.

data.name: smoothLabel9.HelpText
data.value: By default, Asterisk will route the media steams from SIP endpoints through itself. Enabling this option causes asterisk to attempt to negotiate the endpoints to route the media stream directly, bypassing asterisk. It is not always possible for asterisk to negotiate endpoint-to-endpoint media routing.

data.name: smoothLabel8.HelpText
data.value: Check this option if the User or Phone should have 3-Way Calling capability.

data.name: smoothLabel7.HelpText
data.value: Check this option if the User or Phone should have Call-Waiting capability.

data.name: smoothLabel6.HelpText
data.value: Check this option if this User or Phone is a Call Queue Member (Agent)

data.name: smoothLabel4.HelpText
data.value: Check this option if the User or Phone is using IAX or is an IAX device.

data.name: smoothLabel3.HelpText
data.value: Check this option if the User or Phone is using SIP or is a SIP device.

data.name: smoothLabel2.HelpText
data.value: Check this option if the user is to be listed in the system telephone directory.

data.name: smoothLabel1.HelpText
data.value: Check this box if the user should have a voicemail account.

data.name: insecureLabel.HelpText
data.value: Insecure options, Port: allows matching of peers by IP address without matching port number. Invite: removes the requirement for authentication of incoming INVITE messages. Port,Invite: allows both the matching of peers by IP address without matching port number and removes the requirement for authentication of incoming INVITE messages. No: requires normal IP-based matching and authenticated INVITES.

data.name: dtmfmodeLabel.HelpText
data.value:
Set default dtmfmode for sending DTMF. Default: rfc2833
Other options, info : SIP INFO messages inband : Inband audio (requires 64 kbit codec -alaw, ulaw) auto : Use rfc2833 if offered, inband otherwise

data.name: extensionLabel.HelpText
data.value: The numbered extension, i.e. 1234, that will be associated with this particular User / Phone.

data.name: fullNameLabel.HelpText
data.value: A character-based name for this user, i.e. "Bob Jones"

data.name: contextLabel.HelpText
data.value: Please choose the DialPlan for this user. DialPlans are sets of calling rules and can be managed form the "Dial Plans" panel.

data.name: vmsecretLabel.HelpText
data.value: Voicemail Password for this user, Ex: "1234".

data.name: passwordLabel.HelpText
data.value: The password for the user's sip/iax account , Ex: "12u3b6"

data.name: emailLabel.HelpText
data.value: The e-mail address for this user, i.e. "bobjones@bobjones.null"

data.name: cidNumberLabel.HelpText
data.value: The Caller ID (CID) string used when this user calls another internal user.

data.name: zapchanLabel.HelpText
data.value: If this user is attached to an analog port on the system, please choose the port number here.
